00:49:25.949 --> 00:49:29.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our son, Isaac.

00:49:32.581 --> 00:49:36.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sarah’s miraculous pregnancy and Isaac’s birth

00:49:36.251 --> 00:49:38.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
were proof that Jehovah’s word

00:49:38.253 --> 00:49:40.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
always comes true.

00:49:52.309 --> 00:49:54.061 line:90% position:50% align:center
As the rains came down,

00:49:59.525 --> 00:50:02.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
there they were, eight souls,

00:50:02.778 --> 00:50:05.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
safe on the ark.

00:50:05.531 --> 00:50:07.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah protected Noah’s family.

00:50:09.827 --> 00:50:12.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s why we’re alive today.

00:50:16.500 --> 00:50:19.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you know, that’s not the only time.

00:50:19.670 --> 00:50:22.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
There have been many things that seemed scary.

00:50:25.218 --> 00:50:27.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jehovah always

00:50:27.303 --> 00:50:29.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
makes sure his promises come true.

00:50:31.057 --> 00:50:33.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
Think how he helped to protect your mother

00:50:35.937 --> 00:50:38.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
when Pharaoh wanted to take her as his wife.

00:50:38.982 --> 00:50:42.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
Think how he sent angels to save Lot.

00:50:44.988 --> 00:50:47.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember he caused your birth.

00:50:49.951 --> 00:50:53.580 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m your father, but Jehovah is your Father too.

00:50:55.790 --> 00:50:58.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
You are part of his purpose, Isaac.

00:50:58.084 --> 00:51:01.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hard things are going to happen,

00:51:01.004 --> 00:51:04.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
but remember we can always trust Jehovah.

00:51:05.675 --> 00:51:07.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because he always keeps his promises.

00:51:07.052 --> 00:51:08.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right!

00:51:08.970 --> 00:51:11.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember the promise Jehovah made to our family?

00:51:11.848 --> 00:51:14.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will give to you

00:51:14.309 --> 00:51:16.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and to your offspring after you

00:51:16.603 --> 00:51:19.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the land in which you lived as a . . . lasting possession,

00:51:19.856 --> 00:51:22.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I will be their God.”

00:51:24.319 --> 00:51:25.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
Come here.

00:51:39.209 --> 00:51:41.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hard things did happen,

00:51:41.128 --> 00:51:43.881 line:90% position:50% align:center
even in this spiritual household.

00:51:45.132 --> 00:51:48.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am the star. I am the firstborn.

00:51:48.135 --> 00:51:50.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everybody hates you. Nobody likes you.

00:51:50.262 --> 00:51:52.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our father loves me. The joke is on you, Isaac.

00:51:52.848 --> 00:51:54.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am the firstborn.

00:51:54.975 --> 00:51:57.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
No one cares about you, not even God.

00:51:57.269 --> 00:51:59.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
The dancing is for me.

00:52:00.564 --> 00:52:03.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everybody hates you. Nobody likes you.

00:52:03.401 --> 00:52:06.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
This wasn’t just sibling rivalry.

00:52:06.028 --> 00:52:09.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ishmael’s abusive behavior had broken Sarah’s heart.

00:52:09.782 --> 00:52:11.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please, please, please,

00:52:11.826 --> 00:52:15.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
drive out that slave girl and her son.

00:52:23.421 --> 00:52:25.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not be displeased

00:52:25.423 --> 00:52:28.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
by what Sarah is saying to you

00:52:28.092 --> 00:52:31.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
about the boy and about your slave girl.

00:52:31.513 --> 00:52:33.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
Listen to her,

00:52:33.640 --> 00:52:35.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
for what will be called your offspring

00:52:35.934 --> 00:52:38.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be through Isaac.

00:52:38.311 --> 00:52:40.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
As for the son of the slave girl,

00:52:40.647 --> 00:52:42.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
I will also make a nation out of him,

00:52:42.857 --> 00:52:45.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
because he is your offspring.

00:52:54.661 --> 00:52:56.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though it was hard,

00:52:56.955 --> 00:52:58.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham obediently sent Hagar

00:52:58.957 --> 00:53:01.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his son Ishmael away,

00:53:03.045 --> 00:53:05.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
trusting that Jehovah had his eyes upon them.

00:53:22.439 --> 00:53:24.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham!

00:53:26.360 --> 00:53:27.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here I am!

00:53:28.612 --> 00:53:31.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
Take, please, your son,

00:53:31.240 --> 00:53:34.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
your only son whom you so love, Isaac,

00:53:34.577 --> 00:53:36.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
and travel to the land of Moriah

00:53:36.829 --> 00:53:39.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
and offer him up there as a burnt offering

00:53:39.999 --> 00:53:42.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
on one of the mountains that I will designate to you.

00:54:36.056 --> 00:54:37.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s go.

00:54:41.561 --> 00:54:43.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the past,

00:54:43.897 --> 00:54:45.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham had asked God questions

00:54:45.899 --> 00:54:49.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
about some of his judgments and decisions,

00:54:49.528 --> 00:54:52.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
but now his friendship and trust in Jehovah

00:54:52.823 --> 00:54:54.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
had grown.

00:54:54.449 --> 00:54:56.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
He didn’t ask anything at all.

00:54:59.830 --> 00:55:01.832 line:90% position:50% align:center
You stay here with the donkey,

00:55:01.832 --> 00:55:03.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
but the boy and I will go over there

00:55:03.167 --> 00:55:05.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
and worship and return to you.

00:55:16.138 --> 00:55:17.306 line:90% position:50% align:center
Father!

00:55:18.057 --> 00:55:19.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, my son!

00:55:21.227 --> 00:55:24.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here are the fire and the wood,

00:55:24.021 --> 00:55:26.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
but where is the sheep

00:55:26.357 --> 00:55:27.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the burnt offering?

00:55:37.410 --> 00:55:39.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
God himself will provide the sheep

00:55:39.495 --> 00:55:41.497 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the burnt offering, my son.

00:57:51.880 --> 00:57:54.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham, Abraham!

00:57:54.257 --> 00:57:55.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here I am!

00:57:55.592 --> 00:57:58.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not harm the boy,

00:57:58.720 --> 00:58:00.972 line:90% position:50% align:center
and do not do anything at all to him,

00:58:03.058 --> 00:58:07.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
for now I do know that you are God-fearing

00:58:07.020 --> 00:58:09.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
because you have not withheld your son,

00:58:09.689 --> 00:58:12.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
your only one, from me.

00:59:12.336 --> 00:59:14.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
And by means of your offspring

00:59:14.964 --> 00:59:16.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
all nations of the earth

00:59:16.966 --> 00:59:19.969 line:90% position:50% align:center
will obtain a blessing for themselves

00:59:19.969 --> 00:59:22.972 line:90% position:50% align:center
because you have listened to my voice.

00:59:23.806 --> 00:59:25.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abraham

00:59:25.099 --> 00:59:27.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Sarah

00:59:27.435 --> 00:59:28.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Isaac

00:59:28.895 --> 00:59:31.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
all knew they could have full faith in Jehovah.

00:59:33.358 --> 00:59:37.695 line:90% position:50% align:center
His promises to them are promises to us.

00:59:44.619 --> 00:59:48.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we immerse ourselves
in familiar Bible accounts,

00:59:48.331 --> 00:59:52.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
we gain an even deeper appreciation
for their power

00:59:52.043 --> 00:59:54.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
and more firmly embed in our hearts

00:59:54.713 --> 00:59:57.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
the lessons we learn from them.

00:59:57.465 --> 01:00:01.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this month’s postcard,
we’ll visit our brothers in Lesotho,

01:00:01.303 --> 01:00:04.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
a country in the south of Africa.

01:00:04.556 --> 01:00:07.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lesotho is over 1,000 meters,

01:00:07.100 --> 01:00:10.937 line:90% position:50% align:center
or 3,280 feet, above sea level,

01:00:10.937 --> 01:00:15.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
with some of its mountain peaks
rising three times as high.

01:00:15.525 --> 01:00:18.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
The majority of its two million people,

01:00:18.111 --> 01:00:20.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
called Basotho, live in rural areas.

01:00:21.657 --> 01:00:24.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many herd animals or farm for a living.

01:00:24.952 --> 01:00:30.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
Weather conditions can change quickly
in Lesotho’s mountainous terrain,

01:00:30.207 --> 01:00:33.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
calling for protection from sudden cold.

01:00:34.336 --> 01:00:38.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the famous Basotho blanket
comes in quite handy,

01:00:38.048 --> 01:00:40.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
especially in winter 

01:00:40.050 --> 01:00:42.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
when the mountains are blanketed in snow.

01:00:43.804 --> 01:00:48.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, the good news must be spread
despite cold or heights

01:00:48.267 --> 01:00:52.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
as our brothers there have been doing
for over 80 years.

01:00:52.021 --> 01:00:54.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1942,

01:00:54.065 --> 01:00:58.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
two Basotho Witnesses
who learned the truth in South Africa

01:00:58.486 --> 01:01:03.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
returned to preach enthusiastically
in this challenging territory.

01:01:03.199 --> 01:01:07.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nine years later,
there were five small congregations

01:01:07.203 --> 01:01:09.580 line:90% position:50% align:center
with 63 Witnesses.

01:01:09.580 --> 01:01:11.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the 1960’s and 1970’s,

01:01:11.666 --> 01:01:15.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
the work continued
thanks to the tireless efforts

01:01:15.712 --> 01:01:17.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
of zealous evangelizers.

01:01:18.298 --> 01:01:21.134 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, over 3,700 publishers

01:01:21.134 --> 01:01:25.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
conduct over 4,500 Bible studies

01:01:25.221 --> 01:01:27.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
each month.

01:01:27.765 --> 01:01:32.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because Lesotho’s population is widely spread
across a challenging terrain,

01:01:32.312 --> 01:01:36.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
our brothers exert themselves to preach

01:01:36.358 --> 01:01:39.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
wherever the people live.

01:01:39.027 --> 01:01:41.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many of our brothers here climb steep paths

01:01:41.947 --> 01:01:44.241 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get to their meetings

01:01:44.241 --> 01:01:47.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
—especially the 78 publishers

01:01:47.202 --> 01:01:49.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Mokhotlong Congregation,

01:01:49.913 --> 01:01:53.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
who meet in the highest Kingdom Hall
in southern Africa.

01:01:54.960 --> 01:01:57.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the heights of Lesotho,

01:01:57.295 --> 01:02:01.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
the brothers and sisters
of the Mokhotlong Congregation

01:02:01.967 --> 01:02:05.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
send you their warmest greetings.

01:02:05.220 --> 01:02:08.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:02:08.932 --> 01:02:13.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

